[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T21:44:29+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/Untitled-design-2024-10-01T172300.765.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Valheim</em> is a fun crafting survival game to play with a group of pals set in the Viking afterlife, and the board game adaptation is off to a great start. On Tuesday, a crowdfunding campaign for <em>Valheim: The Board Game</em> went live on Gamefound, and it already hit 300% funding. There are no stretch goals for the game, as the developer is choosing to deliver a complete, core experience \u2014 but there are some fun goodies that players can pledge for, along with the game itself.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24180447/valheim-the-board-game-mood-publishing-crowdfunding\">We interviewed developer Ole S", "id": 1250023, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/459047/valheim-board-game-crowdfunder-gamefound", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Valheim board game smashes crowdfunding goals on first day", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T21:32:03+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23230414/NSW_OLED_Model_lifestyle_11.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The makers of the Nintendo Switch emulator Ryujinx pulled the open-source project offline after being contacted by Nintendo, one of its developer announced Tuesday on Discord. If you\u2019re counting, that\u2019s the second Nintendo Switch emulator to be pulled offline in 2024; Nintendo <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24085140/nintendo-totk-leaked-yuzu-lawsuit-emulator\">sued the makers of popular open source emulator Yuzu</a> in February <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24090351/nintendo-2-4-million-yuzu-switch-emulator-settlement-lawsuit\">before settling for a $2.4 million payout in March</a>.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"", "id": 1250024, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/458905/nintendo-switch-emulator-ryujinx-offline", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nintendo Switch emulator Ryujinx taken offline", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T20:18:59+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/vlcsnap-2024-10-01-14h49m20s757.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The <strong>Eternal Forest </strong>is one of the later areas in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/the-legend-of-zelda-echoes-of-wisdom/40934\">The Legend of Zelda: Echoes of Wisdom</a></em>, but you can visit it early in the game if you\u2019re feeling adventurous.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">There are a few things to know if you\u2019re in the Eternal Forest and wondering, \u201cWhat\u2019s going on in here?\u201d For one, is the area for the almost-last part of the game. You\u2019ll need to clear out the\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/zelda-echoes-wisdom-guides/454230/lanayru-temple-walkthrough-dungeon-stilled-hebra-mountain\">Hebra Mountains</a>, the\u00a0<a href=\"", "id": 1249572, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/zelda-echoes-wisdom-guides/458630/eternal-forest-walkthrough-orb-puzzle-solution", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Eternal Forest walkthrough in Zelda: Echoes of Wisdom", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T19:02:24+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"Arthur, a young Black man with glasses who\u2019s wearing a grey shirt, looks out the rain-streaked windows of his apartment in the game Apartment Story.\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/ss_00864086d63bedbff9c55af20b43bf2719c3da9c-1.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption>Arthur, a young Black man with glasses who\u2019s wearing a grey shirt, looks out the rain-streaked windows of his apartment in the game Apartment Story.</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/app/3069870/Apartment_Story/\"><em>Apartment Story</em> is a short, cinematic game on Steam</a> that feels at first like a life simulator, but corrupts the domestic fantasy with a threat, an intruder, and a gun. It starts out all fun and games as I assume the role of Arthur, a guy with no plans for the day a", "id": 1248872, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/impressions/458766/apartment-story-narrative-thriller-game-pc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apartment Story is a short, dramatic thriller with life sim elements", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T18:49:42+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A collage featuring the Amazon Luna controller, the Amazon Fire HD 10 tablet, Anker\u2019s Prime 12,000mAh portable battery, and Corsair\u2019s MP600 Mini 2 TB M.2 SSD.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Cameron Faulkner/Polygon | Source images: Amazon, Anker, Corsair\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/earlyPDdeals.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">It\u2019s October, which in the world of shopping means that we\u2019re getting awfully close to the avalanche of savings that come with Black Friday and Cyber Monday \u2014\u00a0but before <em>that</em>, however, Amazon is celebrating the start of fall with <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/amazon-prime-day/452105/october-amazon-prime-day-2024-dates\">October Prime Day</a>, a tradition from the past few years that gives shoppers a taste of this season\u2019s best deals.", "id": 1248873, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/amazon-prime-day/458471/best-early-deals-board-games-toys", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best early October Prime Day deals", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T18:46:50+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/inscryption.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Game Pass is clearly celebrating October in style by teeing up a creepy old Polygon favorite, <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/22843002/inscryption-best-video-game-2021-polygon-goty\">Inscryption</a></em>, to be <a href=\"https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2024/10/01/xbox-game-pass-october-2024-wave-1/\">released on the platform</a> on Oct. 10. <em>Inscryption</em> is not your typical horror game \u2014 it doesn\u2019t exactly have jump scares \u2014 but the far-reaching tendrils of its fictional premise definitely filled me with unease when I played it back in 2021. It starts out as a simplified roguelite card game played against a mysterious, dimly lit opponent. Of course, you\u2019re playing ", "id": 1248874, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/458736/inscryption-xbox-pc-game-pass-october-10", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Inscryption, Polygon\u2019s 2021 game of the year, heads to Game Pass", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T18:00:49+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A collage of different Zelda\u2019s throughout the series, including The Legend of Zelda, Breath of the Wild, A Link to the Past, Wand of Gamelon, Ocarina of Time, Windwaker, and Echoes of Wisdom.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/ZeldaThumbNoBorder.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/review/455289/legend-of-zelda-echoes-of-wisdom-review-nintendo-switch\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.polygon.com/review/455289/legend-of-zelda-echoes-of-wisdom-review-nintendo-switch\">The Legend of Zelda: Echoes of Wisdom</a></em> is a big deal for the franchise because it\u2019s finally the first mainline game where you get to play as Princess Zelda. Yes, despite her name being the dang title of the series, she\u2019s never been the main ch", "id": 1248383, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/zelda/458224/a-brief-history-of-nintendo-not-letting-you-play-as-zelda", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "A brief history of Nintendo not letting you play as Zelda", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T18:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A headshot of Akihiko Yamashita overlaid on a screenshot from Lupin the 3rd: The Castle of Cagliostro\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Graphic: Will Joel/Polygon | Image sources: Studio Ghibli\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/Akihiko-Yamashita.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Akihiko Yamashita, who\u2019s worked on titles as wide reaching as <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/anime/446097/toonami-original-anime-rick-morty-uzumaki-history\">The Big O</a></em> and <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/22633960/rebuild-evangelion-movies-ending\">Evangelion 2.0</a></em>, has quite the anime resume. Since 2001, he\u2019s been working with Studio Ghibli, having done work on <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23689921/spirited-away-live-on-stage-director-interview-john-caird\">Spirited Away</a> </", "id": 1248384, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/anime/458153/studio-ghibli-miyazaki-yamashita-lupin-3rd-favorite", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "My Favorite Anime: Studio Ghibli animator Akihiko Yamatsura on the anime that changed his life", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T17:43:19+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A tall ghoulish-looking man standing at the far end of a crowded subway car in Crowded. Followed.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Shane Ferry/Night Dial\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/ejFDGQ.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">It\u2019s October, which means you\u2019re likely getting in the mood for Halloween later this month by watching, reading, or playing any number of horror or horror-adjacent media right now. In addition to all the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24090384/best-horror-movies-2024-how-scary\">exciting (and terrifying) movies</a> released this year, there are also plenty of terrific horror games to choose from like <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gaming/445539/how-hollowbodys-developer-draws-on-silent-hills-legacy-to-craft-a-new-generation-of-horrors\"><em>Hollowbo", "id": 1248385, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/horror/458703/crowded-followed-survival-horror-game-it-follows", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Somebody made the video game equivalent of It Follows and it looks awesome", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T17:21:34+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/jlee_241001_1001_pogo_max_battles.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">If you\u2019re looking to expand your inventory of <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-go-guide/449273/dynamax-pokemon-get-catch-max-battles\">Dynamax Pok\u00e9mon</a> in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/pokemon-go/38713\">Pok\u00e9mon Go</a></em>, you\u2019ll want to know what\u2019s available every month.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">It does appear that Niantic will start rotating Pok\u00e9mon in and out of <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-go-guide/447529/max-particles-power-spots-how-to-get-mp\">Max Battles</a> on a month-by-month basis, with some event Pok\u00e9mon littered in.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">That being said, you\u2019ll want a healthy a", "id": 1248386, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-go-guide/458543/max-battle-schedule-dynamax", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Pok\u00e9mon Go Max Battle schedule for October 2024", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T17:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A symbol in the shape of an eye, with a crescent moon in the pupil. The background is purple.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Night Vale Presents\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/WtoNV-Eye-copy.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\"><em>Welcome To Night Vale</em>, regarded by our sister site Vulture as \u201c<a href=\"https://www.vulture.com/article/best-fiction-pocasts-all-time.html\">the foundational institution of the fiction-podcast genre</a>,\u201d is getting its first official adaptation as a tabletop role-playing game. Currently in production by Renegade Game Studios (publishers of <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/tabletop-games/23962341/vampire-the-masquerade-bleed-controversy-explained\">Vampire: The Masquerade</a></em>, <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2020/8/2", "id": 1248387, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/preview/458385/welcome-to-night-vale-ttrpg-backerkit-campaign-preview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Buy the Welcome to Night Vale role-playing game for the faceless old woman who secretly lives in your home", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T15:15:08+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Lego\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25554486/zmbov6b8.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>While the gamified version of Lego Super Mario continues to expand with new and <a href=\"https://www.lego.com/en-us/product/the-bowser-express-train-71437\">increasingly complex playsets</a>, more traditional Lego sets inspired by the red plumber are somewhat rare. However, you can now pick up a new set featuring a caped Mario astride his trusty mount Yoshi. The $129.99 <a href=\"https://www.lego.com/en-us/product/tbd-super-mario-2024-11-71438\">Super Mario World: Mario &amp; Yoshi</a> set includes some surprises that we\u2019ll detail below, and joins the ranks of other cool Nintendo sets, like the <a href=\"https://www.lego.com/en-us/product/super-mario-64-questi", "id": 1247390, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/24210679/lego-super-mario-yoshi-set-pre-order-where-to-buy", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "You can now buy the Lego Super Mario &#038; Yoshi set", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T15:13:43+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Graphic: Julia Lee/Polygon | Source images: Game Freak/Nintendo, The Pok\u00e9mon Company\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/jlee_241001_1001_pogo_raids.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>Using a<strong> raid schedule </strong>helps you work out which creatures to save your raid passes (remote or otherwise) for in <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-go-guide\"><em>Pok\u00e9mon Go</em></a>.</p>\n\n<p>The <strong>raid targets</strong> swap out every 10 days approximately, so you\u2019ll definitely want to keep track on who is coming next.</p>\n\n<p>If you\u2019re unfamiliar with raids, they spawn in gyms from <strong>10 a.m. until 10 p.m. local time</strong>. After the timer ticks down, a raid target will appear. You can check the difficulty of a raid while it\u2019s still a egg; five-star raids have five", "id": 1247391, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-go-guide/24168766/raid-schedule-legendary-mega-shadow-five-star", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Pok\u00e9mon Go raid schedule for October 2024\u2019s Legendary and Mega Pok\u00e9mon", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T14:29:11+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Hoyoverse via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24612363/StarRail_2023_04_18_13_12_06.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/honkai-star-rail/40897\">Honkai: Star Rail</a></em> is Hoyoverse\u2019s latest title added to their mobile (and PC) game lineup, which means that yes, the game has codes that you can redeem for premium currency.</p>\n\n<p>In this case, <strong><em>Honkai: Star Rail</em> codes</strong> reward Stellar Jade and the usual other goodies \u2014 money, EXP, and the like.</p>\n\n<p>Below we list out the currently active <em>Honkai: Star Rail</em> redemption codes as of<strong> October 2024</strong> and explain how to redeem codes.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\" />\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-b", "id": 1246844, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/honkai-star-rail-guides/23699079/code-redeem-redemption-gift-stellar-jade", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Honkai: Star Rail codes for October 2024", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T14:10:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Epic Games\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/Fortnite_20210807141447.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Epic Games <a href=\"https://www.epicgames.com/site/en-US/news/introducing-time-limit-controls-and-time-reports-for-fortnite-and-uefn\">released two new parental control features</a> on Tuesday: time limits and time reports. Now, parents are able to monitor and limit how much time their kids spend in <em>Fortnite</em>.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The new controls can be found in the Parental Controls section of <em>Fortnite</em>\u2019s menu, or on a browser in the Epic Account Portal. This is where a parent or guardian is able to limit daily <em>Fortnite</em> time, pick windows of time a child can play, and allow (or not) their kid to reque", "id": 1246845, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/fortnite/458468/fortnite-epic-games-time-limits-parental-controls", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Your mom can now set you Fortnite time limits", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/ss_bfa3b19d302ec11f4d6c50af7797ef91e4f3dc32.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Game creator Yoko Taro, best known for his game <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2017/3/6/14735646/nier-automata-review-ps4-playstation-4-windows-pc-square-enix-yoko-taro-platinum-games\">Nier: Automata</a></em> and his commitment to wearing a mask in public, recently shared high praise about Katsura Hashino, producer and director of the Persona series. \u201cHashino really knows his stuff,\u201d <a href=\"https://youtu.be/m5ISZboP4CM?t=768\">Taro said</a>. \u201cHe believes that games are essential to making the world a better place.\u201d</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Hashino\u2019s new game, <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/impressions/444848/metaph", "id": 1246846, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/458378/metaphor-refantazio-interview-katsura-hashino", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Can Metaphor: ReFantazio change the world, just a little bit? Its creator hopes so", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T13:55:57+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/zelda-echoes-of-wisdom-outfits.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Zelda has several <strong>outfits </strong>she can wear in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/the-legend-of-zelda-echoes-of-wisdom/40934\">The Legend of Zelda: Echoes of Wisdom</a></em>. Though most of them have no effect on the gameplay, who wouldn\u2019t want to look their best while saving Hyrule?</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The outfits are all locked behind different means, whether it\u2019s story progression, amiibos, or side quests. Below we discuss how to unlock all the outfits in <em>Echoes of Wisdom</em>.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" />\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"all-outfits-list-in-zelda-echoes-of-", "id": 1246847, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/zelda-echoes-wisdom-guides/458047/unlock-all-outfits-locations", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Where to unlock all outfits in Zelda: Echoes of Wisdom", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T13:52:39+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/Lego-Star-Wars-box.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">I know what you\u2019re thinking: It\u2019s not even Halloween yet. It\u2019s not even Thanksgiving yet. We haven\u2019t even had the Nightmare <em>Before </em>Christmas, much less had to think of December festivities. And yet \u2014&nbsp;<em>and yet</em> \u2014&nbsp;I am writing to tell you that it\u2019s time to start preparing for the holidays. The 2024 Lego Star Wars Advent calendar is here and, if you <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0CV287MYQ/\">order from Amazon</a>, you can save 20% off the list price and pick it up for $35.99 (was $44.99).</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">We\u2019re <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/deals/23960913/nerdy-advent-calendars-best-mario-funko-pokemon-sta", "id": 1246848, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/good-deals/458473/lego-star-wars-advent-calendar-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The 2024 Lego Star Wars Advent Calendar is delightful \u2014 and it\u2019s 20% off", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A 31-day calendar filled with scary movie images, over an image of glowing jack-o-lanterns and bats.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Graphic: Will Joel/Polygon | Source images: Various\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/10_1_Halloween-Header.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Do you feel that? That chill in the air, that tingling sensation at the back of your neck? It can only mean one thing. That\u2019s right: Halloween season is once again upon us!</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Here at Polygon, we <em>love</em> horror. We cover it <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/horror\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.polygon.com/horror\">all year round</a>, whether it\u2019s ranking the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24090384/best-horror-movies-2024-how-scary\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https:/", "id": 1246376, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/what-to-watch/452010/best-halloween-horror-movies-tv-watch-stream", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Halloween Countdown: 31 days of horror to watch", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T11:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/Tomb_Raider__The_Legend_of_Lara_Croft_u_S1_E2_00_15_43_03.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Even with Netflix\u2019s recommendation algorithm serving you new movies, new TV shows, and original programming tailored to your viewing habits, the streaming service\u2019s fire hose of content makes what\u2019s coming difficult to parse.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">A lot of horror movies from the back catalogue \u2014 including <em>Halloween </em>(2018), <em>Scream</em> (2022), and<em> It Chapter Two</em> \u2014 arrive on Netflix just in time for Halloween! But if you prefer your October to be light on scares, don\u2019t worry: there\u2019s also a new season of <em>Heartstopper</em>. The new <em>Ranma 1/2</em> anime, a Lara Croft series, and also t", "id": 1245443, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/entertainment/458016/ew-netflix-october-2024-movies-tv-to-watch", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Every movie and show coming to Netflix in October", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T10:36:40+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A stack of Pok\u00e9Coins and the Field Research icon on a striped background.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/jlee_240830_1001_pogo_coin_bundle.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">\u201c<strong>Daily Pok\u00e9Coin Bounty Ticket</strong> <strong>Part 2</strong>\u201d is available to purchase as part of <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/pokemon-go/38713\">Pok\u00e9mon Go</a></em>\u2019s \u201c<a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-go-guide/446305/max-out-season-start-time-date\">Max Out</a>\u201d season between Oct. and Nov. 2024.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The $4.99 ticket promises a lot of perks, but is it worth buying? We explain what the ticket rewards, along with whether or not your money, below.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" />\n\n<h2 cl", "id": 1245444, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-go-guide/446377/daily-pokecoin-bounty-ticket-worth-it-value-research", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Is the Daily Pok\u00e9Coin Bounty Part 2 ticket worth it in Pok\u00e9mon Go?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T09:06:32+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/vlcsnap-2024-09-30-16h36m50s229.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The <strong>Gerudo Sanctum chest behind the wall</strong> in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/the-legend-of-zelda-echoes-of-wisdom/40934\">The Legend of Zelda: Echoes of Wisdom</a></em> is one of the trickier puzzles to solve at first glance.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">As you journey through the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/zelda-echoes-wisdom-guides/451934/gerudo-sanctum-walkthrough-chests-dungeon-map\">Gerudo Sanctum</a>, you\u2019ll run into a room with some pots. A wall will split the room in half, and you\u2019ll see an <strong>out-of-reach chest on the other side of the wall</strong>. You may try to summon <a href=\"https://www.polygon", "id": 1244696, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/zelda-echoes-wisdom-guides/458305/gerudo-sanctum-chest-behind-the-wall-2f", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to get the Gerudo Sanctum chest behind the wall in Zelda: Echoes of Wisdom", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-01T04:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/jlee_240930_1001_pogo_shiny_pidove.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Pidove</strong>, the tiny pigeon Pok\u00e9mon from Unova, can be found in the wild in <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/pokemon-go/38713\"><em>Pok\u00e9mon Go</em></a>. Yes, <strong>Pidove can be shiny</strong> in <em>Pok\u00e9mon Go</em>!</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Unfezant actually has some stark visual differences between its male and female form. Male Unfezant has that red mask-like plumage on their heads, and female Unfezant doesn\u2019t. This makes it a bit rougher for shiny collectors who may want both of these forms.</p>\n<img src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/jlee_240930_1001_pogo_shiny_pidove_tranquill_u", "id": 1243758, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-go/458030/can-pidove-be-shiny-tranquill-unfezant", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Can Pidove be shiny in Pok\u00e9mon Go?", "vote": 0}]